extends layout

block content
  div(class='container')
    h1 API Basejump: Timestamp microservice
    blockquote User stories:
      ol
        li.
          I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string
          contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016)
        li If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
        li If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
    h3 Example usage:
    code
      a(href='/December%2015,%202015' target='_blank') http://localhost:5000/December%2015,%202015
    br
    code
      a(href='/1450137600' target='_blank') http://localhost:5000/1450137600
    h3 Example output:
    code
      pre.
        {
          "unix": 1450137600,
          "natural": "December 15, 2015"
        }
    p check out source code at:
      a(href='https://github.com/frankbearzou/timestamp-api' target='_blank') https://github.com/frankbearzou/timestamp-api